"><text:span text:style-name="Strong_20_Emphasis"><text:span text:style-name="T3">Designed reusable enterprise data assets</text:span></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T8"> —including the </text:span><text:span text:style-name="Emphasis"><text:span text:style-name="T8">Field Inventory Report</text:span></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T8">—metadata and end-to-end lineage architecture; authoritative SDW reference and onboarding standard for analysts and engineers in governed reporting and downstream underwriting analytics consumption.</text:span></text:p></text:list-item><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P16"><text:span text:style-name="Strong_20_Emphasis"><text:span text:style-name="T3">Architected an automated ARIMA forecasting platform</text:span></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T8"> for Net Amount at Risk (NAR)—accelerates anomaly visibility and structured portfolio dialogue with actuarial partners versus reactive reconciliation alone; delivered through cloud analytics platforms (including Databricks).</text:span></text:p></text:list-item><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P16"><text:span text:style-name="Strong_20_Emphasis"><text:span text:style-name="T3">Built enterprise-grade statistical outlier detection</text:span></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T8"> using probability density functions (PDFs) to surface large-scale attribute shifts early—less manual triage before actuarial escalation.</text:span></text:p></text:list-item><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P16"><text:span text:style-name="Strong_20_Emphasis"><text:span text:style-name="T3">Developed the organization’s first valuation extract comparison architecture</text:span></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T8"> for repeatable, audit-friendly analysis of valuation movements across time and source systems—replacing brittle one-off reconciliations.</text:span></text:p></text:list-item></text:list><text:p text:style-name="P17"><text:span text:style-name="Strong_20_Emphasis"><text:span text:style-name="T12"/></text:span></text:p><text:h text:style-name="P6" text:outline-level="3"><text:span text:style-name="Strong_20_Emphasis"><text:span text:style-name="T3">Chicago Pneumatic Company LLC</text:span></text:span></text:h><text:p text:style-name="P14"><text:span text:style-name="Strong_20_Emphasis"><text:span text:style-name="T3">Assistant Business Controller</text:span></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T11"> </text:span><text:span text:style-name="T8">| 2012 – 2018</text:span></text:p><text:list text:style-name="L5"><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P18"><text:span text:style-name="T8">Led </text:span><text:span text:style-name="Strong_20_Emphasis"><text:span text:style-name="T3">cross-functional analytics and reporting modernization initiatives</text:span></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T8">, partnering with HR, Sales, Marketing, and Executive Leadership.</text:span></text:p></text:list-item><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P19">Implemented automated reporting that improved accessibility, consistency, and operational efficiency.</text:p></text:list-item><text:list-item><text:p text:style-name="P20"><text:span text:style-name="T8">Served as a </text:span><text:span text:style-name="Strong_20_Emphasis"><text:span text:style-name="T3">bridge between business stakeholders and technical teams</text:span></text:span><text:span text:style-name="T11">,</text:span><text:span text:style-name="T8"> translating executive priorities into measurable outcomes with operational and financial discipline and executive-ready transparency—laying groundwork for subsequent enterprise data and architecture leadership.</text:span></text:p></text:list-item></text:list><text:p text:style-name="P2"><text:soft-page-break/></text:p><text:h text:style-name="P4" text:outline-level="2"><text:span text:style-name="Strong_20_Emphasis"><text:span text:style-name="T8">EDUCATION &amp; CREDENTIALS</text:span></text:span></text:h><